{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-note-post-js","path":"/notes/2019-07-09-webpack-&-microfrontends-/","webpackCompilationHash":"84fe29e572b8dcee481c","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Tan Li Hau","author":"Tan Li Hau"}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<!--\ntag: webpack\n-->\n<p>To silent MiniCssExtractPlugin annoying logs:</p>\n<p class=\"filename\">webpack.config.js</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  stats<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    children<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">false</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><a href=\"https://webpack.js.org/configuration/stats/\">Read more</a> about webpack’s stats configuration</p>\n<!--\ntag: micro-frontend\n-->\n<p><a href=\"https://martinfowler.com/articles/micro-frontends.html\">https://martinfowler.com/articles/micro-frontends.html</a></p>\n<p>Problems:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>If router is asynchronously injected, what should you do when visit a route that is <strong>not yet injected</strong>?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Define a routing schema, eg, when you are visiting <code class=\"language-text\">/foo/bar</code> and your local routing registry does not contain the path, you should visit a predefine location for the script/manifest, eg: <code class=\"language-text\">server.com/sites/foo-bar/manifest.json</code>, and load the script. If there’s no such file, it meant there’s no such path.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Multiple webpack built runtime</p>\n<ul>\n<li>async chunks will rely on the <code class=\"language-text\">window[&#39;webpackJsonp&#39;]</code> to <code class=\"language-text\">require</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">exports</code> module.</li>\n<li>multiple webpack built may have conflicting <code class=\"language-text\">chunkIds</code></li>\n<li>thankfully this can be solved via <a href=\"https://github.com/darshanlsagar/webpack-custom-chunk-id-plugin\">webpack-custom-chunk-id-plugin</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"","fields":{"noteDate":"2019-07-09","noteTitle":"webpack & \"microfrontends\""},"frontmatter":{"title":"","date":null}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/notes/2019-07-09-webpack-&-microfrontends-/","type":"notes","noteDate":"2019-07-09","noteTitle":"webpack & \"microfrontends\"","wip":false,"heroImageUrl":null,"heroTwitterImageUrl":null,"previous":{"id":"769519c6-dc72-5bd5-9d67-70640b63801f","fields":{"slug":"/notes/2019-07-29-babel-plugin-order/","type":"notes","noteDate":"2019-07-29","noteTitle":"babel plugin order","wip":false},"frontmatter":{"title":""}},"next":{"id":"a0af9c6f-b027-5b64-9a02-3b2ed1de0627","fields":{"slug":"/notes/2019-07-03-random/","type":"notes","noteDate":"2019-07-03","noteTitle":"random","wip":false},"frontmatter":{"title":""}}}}}